  "body": "<!--\r\nNeed help?\r\nRefer to our contributing guidelines for additional information about making a good issue:\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum-optimism/.github/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Describe the bug**\r\nWhen sending eth value, we want users to `estimateGas` to get the encoded gasLimit to send their tx with. However, we currently do not allow calling `estimateGas` with no data: https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/blob/8d67991aba584c1703692ea46273ea8a1ef45f56/l2geth/internal/ethapi/api.go#L1024-L1026\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce**\r\nTry calling estimateGas with no calldata.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\nWe can call estimateGas when sending a transaction with ETH value \r\n\r\n**Additional Context**\r\nIt's unclear whether this integration test will set the `gasLimit` to 21,000 by default or if it does call `estimateGas` https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/blob/dcb538d459940a021c580ec33e96a663a972ee49/integration-tests/test/rpc.spec.ts#L102\r\n",
